## Design Decisions & Traceability

| Test Class | Requirement Facet |
|---|---|
| `TestUpdateDemographicsHappyPath` | Clinician can update patient demographics |
| `TestHistoricalVersionPreservation` | All prior versions are stored; history-before-write ordering |
| `TestTimestampBoundaryCases` | Boundary cases on date/time fields (DOB, `updated_at`, leap years, midnight, leap-second approximation) |
| `TestNumericFieldBoundaryCases` | Boundary cases on numeric elements (zero, ±ε, max, overflow, type coercion) |
| `TestAuthorizationAndNotFoundGuards` | Unauthorized or non-existent patients produce no side-effects |
| `TestConcurrentVersionIntegrity` | Sequential updates yield monotonic versions; snapshots hold distinct values |

### Key boundary values covered
- **Weight**: `−0.001`, `0`, `0.001`, `700`, `700.001`, `999 999`, `None`, string, `Decimal`
- **Height**: same pattern up to `300 cm`
- **DOB**: today, today +1 day, `1900-01-01`, leap-day `2000-02-29`, non-leap-year `2001-02-29`, bad formats
- **Timestamps**: midnight, leap-second approximation, UTC-awareness, frozen clock determinism
